         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[Mr. C.  ¶ Hartmann ¶ , the botanist and horticultural collector, has, we are sorry to say, succumbed to fever contracted in New Guinea. He died, as we learn from Baron  ¶ von Müeller ¶ , in Queenslan...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">87.12.00h</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">To the Gardeners' Chronicle</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from 'Mr. Hartmann', </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gardeners' chronicle</seg>
                     <seg style="">, 28 January 1888, p. 114. The letter is dated to December 1887 as the latest that it could have been sent to have been reported in this issue. Hartmann died in Brisbane on 4 December 1887.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Mr. C. </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Hartmann</seg>
               <seg style="">, the botanist and horticultural collector, has, we are sorry to say, succumbed to fever contracted in New Guinea. He died, as we learn from Baron </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">von Müeller</seg>
               <seg style="">, in Queensland, on his return to his home. He and Mr. G. </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Hunter</seg>
               <seg style=""> were the first who brought together a number of native tribes, before always at war with each other, and induced them to act as carriers of the luggage of the travellers at some portions of the Owen Stanley Ranges; and thus they also paved the way for the advent of Mr. </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Abree</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Typesetter's error </seg>
                        <seg style="font-style: italic; ">for</seg> ascent of Mt<seg style="">. Obree?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> by Messrs. </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Cuthbertson</seg>
               <seg style=""> and </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Sayer</seg>
               <seg style="">. At Towamba,</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Typesetter's error for</seg>
                        <seg style=""> Toowoomba.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> in Queensland, Mr. C. </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Hartmann</seg>
               <seg style=""> had a business as a vendor of plants and seeds, and for a long series of years he was interested in obtaining specimens of native plants for the elucidation of the local flora. In former years he had a good repute in Germany as a skilful grower of Orchids. The <name key="Sarcochilus%20Hartmanni">Sarcochilus Hartmanni</name> (S. rubricentrum, Fitzgerald) was discovered by him, and at once named and described in his honour.</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By M, in B</seg>74.10.01, p. 248.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">] </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <name key="Sarcochilus%20Hartmanni">Sarcochilus Hartmanni</name>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <name key="Sarcochilus%20rubricentrum">Sarcochilus rubricentrum</name>
               </seg>
            </p>
